   <a rid="pone.0145285.ref079" ref-type="bibr" href="#pone.0145285.ref079">79</a>]. Recruitment within the model thereby operates as a function of larval dispersal, settlement, and mortality, which is temperature dependent. However, the DBEM does not aim to represent the natural short-term (inter-annual) variability of recruitment; instead it aims to represent the long-term mean changes in production of the population. The intrinsic growth rate of a population is calculated as 
